        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 12:18PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1217 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Evansville, or 8 miles northwest of Greensboro, moving east at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, Akron, Greensboro Municipal Airport, Low Gap, Mertz,
Sawyerville, Heiberger, Wedgeworth, Evansville, Morgan Springs,
Phipps, Harper Hill, Wateroak, Ellards, and Havana.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
